Ozyornoye (; , Köl-Ĵik) is a rural locality (a selo) in the Manzherokskoye Rural Settlement of Mayminsky District, Altai Republic, Russia. The population was 167 as of 2016. There are 36 streets in the locality.
Geography
Ozyornoye is located 34 km south of Mayma (the district's administrative centre) by road. Manzherok is the nearest rural locality.
